The structure of an if/else:

```javascript
if (condition) {
  // runs when condition is true
} else {
  // runs when condition is false
}
```

**Sarah's habit tracker — streak display:**
```javascript
const streakDays = 14;

if (streakDays >= 7) {
  console.log('🔥 You\'re on a roll! ' + streakDays + ' days!');
} else if (streakDays >= 3) {
  console.log('⚡ Getting started! ' + streakDays + ' days.');
} else {
  console.log('Start today. Even 1 day counts.');
}

// Output: 🔥 You're on a roll! 14 days!
```

**Key insight:** `else if` lets you chain multiple conditions. JavaScript checks them in order and runs the first one that's true.

